# TextArea

IDS Text Area allows users to input or edit multiline texts.
IDS Text Area would also allow for validating input, provide suggestions, and help users fix errors.

## Installation & Import

```bash
yarn add @ids-ts/textarea
```

```tsx
import { TextArea } from '@ids-ts/textarea';
```

## Props API

| Prop | Type | Required | Description |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| `automationId` | `string` | No | AutomationID property used for testing purposes |
| `disabled` | `boolean` | No | - |
| `errorText` | `string` | No | Error message to be rendered. |
| `helperText` | `string` | No | Text to be display for extra information |
| `infoText` | `string` | No | Info message to be rendered. |
| `label` | `string` | No | Label to be displayed for the field. |
| `name` | `string` | No | Name to be assigned to the input field. |
| `maxLength` | `number` | No | max length to be assigned to the input field. |
| `onBlur` | `FocusEventHandler<HTMLTextAreaElement>` | No | Prop for handling callBack for onBlur event. |
| `placeholder` | `string` | No | Ghost text for textarea inputs. |
| `size` | `'small' | 'medium'` | No | - |
| `readOnly` | `boolean` | No | - |
| `resizeTextArea` | `boolean` | No | - |
| `value` | `string` | No | Value to be displayed in the input field. |
| `warningText` | `string` | No | warning message to be rendered. |
| `width` | `string` | No | Specifies width of Text Area component. This updates both the Text Area wrapper and input. |

<details>
<summary>Full TypeScript Interface</summary>

```typescript
export interface TextAreaProps extends ThemeableElement<'textarea'> {
  /** AutomationID property used for testing purposes */
  automationId?: string;
  /**
   * Disabled prop to pass on to root when set as true.
   *
   * @default false
   */
  disabled?: boolean;
  /** Error message to be rendered. */
  errorText?: string;
  /** Text to be display for extra information */
  helperText?: string;
  /** Info message to be rendered. */
  infoText?: string;
  /** Label to be displayed for the field. */
  label?: string;
  /** Name to be assigned to the input field. */
  name?: string;
  /** max length to be assigned to the input field. */
  maxLength?: number;
  /** Prop for handling callBack for onBlur event. */
  onBlur?: FocusEventHandler<HTMLTextAreaElement>;
  /** Ghost text for textarea inputs. */
  placeholder?: string;
  /** Affects size of text rendered next to checkbox
   *
   * @default 'medium'
   *
   */
  size?: 'small' | 'medium';
  /**
   * Readonly prop to pass on to root when set as true.
   *
   * @default false
   */
  readOnly?: boolean;
  /**
   * Prop to allow users to set resize as none on textarea.
   *
   * @default true
   */
  resizeTextArea?: boolean;
  /** Value to be displayed in the input field. */
  value?: string;
  /** warning message to be rendered. */
  warningText?: string;
  /** Specifies width of Text Area component. This updates both the Text Area wrapper and input. */
  width?: string;
}
```

</details>

