## Usage Patterns

### Basic

```tsx
() => {
  const [value, setValue] = useState('');

  return (
    <TextArea
      label="Message on invoice"
      placeholder="Thank you for your business and have a great day!"
      value={value}
      automationId="idsTextAreaBasic"
      onChange={(e: any) => setValue(e.target.value)}
    />
  );
}
```

### No Visible Label Use Aria Label For Accessibility

```tsx
() => {
  const [value, setValue] = useState('');

  return (
    <div>
      <h3>No Visible Label Example</h3>
      <TextArea
        placeholder="Thank you for your business and have a great day!"
        aria-label="Message on invoice"
        helperText="Always use a label. In rare case where visible label is not used, use aria-label instead"
        value={value}
        automationId="idsTextAreawithAriaLabel"
        onChange={(e: any) => setValue(e.target.value)}
      />
      <p>
        The element is used to associate a text label with a form field. The
        label is used to tell users the value that should be entered in the
        associated input field. If your design does not include a visible label,
        then you must include an aria-label to provide information to the screen
        reader.
      </p>
    </div>
  );
}
```

